This paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category as it proposes a super-resolution channel estimation scheme for mmWave massive MIMO with hybrid precoding. It also involves the use of low pilot overhead to estimate a low-dimensional effective channel, which is a common technique in information theory. 

It could also belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category as it deals with wireless communications and proposes a technique for improving channel estimation in 5G networks. 

The Signal Processing (cs.SI) sub-category is also a possibility as the paper involves the use of the 2D unitary ESPRIT algorithm for channel estimation, which is a signal processing technique. 

The Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category is another possibility as the paper deals with mmWave communications, which is a technology commonly used for multimedia applications. 

Finally, the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category is a less likely possibility as the paper does not involve natural language processing or any other language-related tasks.
